",, England":"England, United Kingdom","Checkenden, Oxfordshire, England":"Checkendon, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"MARMION","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: perhaps an Anglicized form of an unidentified Gaelic name. Compare   Merriman  .","English (Lancashire; of Norman origin) and French: nickname from Old French <i>marmion</i> ‘monkey, brat’."],"variants":[{"name":"Merriman","meanings":["English:","nickname from Middle English <i>mirie</i>, <i>merie</i>, <i>murie</i> ‘merry, pleasant’ + <i>man</i> ‘man’. Compare   Merry   1. This surname is established in Ireland (perhaps as an Anglicized form of an unidentified Gaelic name; compare   Marmion  ) as well as England.","there has probably been some confusion with <b>Marriman</b>, probably an occupational name meaning ‘servant of <i>Mary</i>’, from the female personal name <i>Mary</i> (see   Marie  ) + Middle English <i>man</i> in the sense ‘servant’, or perhaps a pet form of <i>Mary</i> using the hypocoristic suffix -<i>man</i>. The surname <i>Marriman</i> is now vanishingly rare in Britain and Ireland."]},{"name":"Marmon","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Gloucestershire):","variant of   Marmion  .","variant of <b>Marriman</b>, an occupational name meaning ‘servant of Mary’, from the female personal name <i>Mary</i> (see   Marie  ) + Middle English <i>man</i> in the sense ‘servant’."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs William MARMION was born about 1160, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with William Marmion Lord of Checkenden."},"et":{"Abt 1160–":"umbes 1160–Surnud","1155–1220":"1155–1220","1198–1246":"1198–1246","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","1246":"1246","1155":"1155","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","Abt 1160":"umbes 1160","1160":"1160",",, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Checkenden, Oxfordshire, England":"Checkendon, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1160–":"noin 1160–Kuollut","1155–1220":"1155–1220","1198–1246":"1198–1246","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","1246":"1246","1155":"1155","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","Abt 1160":"noin 1160","1160":"1160",",, England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Checkenden, Oxfordshire, England":"Checkendon, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1160–":"environ 1160–Décédée","1155–1220":"1155–1220","1198–1246":"1198–1246","1160–Female":"1160–Décédée","1246":"1246","1155":"1155","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","Abt 1160":"environ 1160","1160":"1160",",, England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Checkenden, Oxfordshire, England":"Checkendon, Oxfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs William MARMION est née environ 1160, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec William Marmion Lord of Checkenden."},"de":{"Abt 1160–":"um 1160–Verstorben","1155–1220":"1155–1220","1198–1246":"1198–1246","1160–Female":"1160–Verstorben","1246":"1246","1155":"1155","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","Abt 1160":"um 1160","1160":"1160",",, England":"England, United Kingdom","Checkenden, Oxfordshire, England":"Checkendon, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mrs William MARMION wurde um 1160 in England, United Kingdom ge